# ✅ Why Use SSH Keys for Git?
- SSH (Secure Shell) keys provide a secure way to authenticate with Git servers (e.g., GitHub, GitLab) without typing your username and password every time. They are more secure and convenient than HTTPS authentication, especially for push/pull operations.
# 🔍 Step-by-Step Explanation
## 🔎 Step 1: Check for Existing SSH Keys
```
ls -al ~/.ssh
```
